'''无政府共产主义'''{{efn|或称'''共产无政府主义'''<ref>{{cite journal |author1=W Haixia |title=无政府主义思想与乡村改造的实践回顾——从消去的无政府主义提取当代价值 |journal=''Rural China'' |date=2014-06-07 |volume=11 |issue=2 |pages=301–327 |doi=10.1163/22136746-12341256 |url=https://brill.com/view/journals/rchs/11/2/article-p301_4.xml |accessdate=2021-02-20}}</ref>（{{lang-en|communist anarchism}}<ref>[http://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/wendy-mcelroy-the-schism-between-individualist-and-communist-anarchism "The Schism Between Individualist and Communist Anarchism"] {{Wayback|url=http://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/wendy-mcelroy-the-schism-between-individualist-and-communist-anarchism |date=20210416071607 }} by [[溫蒂·莫艾洛依|Wendy McElroy]].</ref><ref>"Anarchist communism is also known as anarcho-communism, communist anarchism, or, sometimes, libertarian communism". "Anarchist communism - an introduction" by Jacques Roux.</ref>）、'''自由共产主义'''<ref>{{cite journal |author1=羽离子 |title=欧文的实验村——新兰那克的今昔 |journal=《湖北民族学院学报(哲学社会科学版)》 |date=2003 |volume=21 |issue=3 |pages=6-9 |doi=10.13501/j.cnki.42-1328/c.2003.03.002 |url=https://www.cnki.com.cn/Article/CJFDTOTAL-HBZA200303002.htm |accessdate=2021-02-20 |archive-date=2019-06-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190615063230/http://www.cnki.com.cn/Article/CJFDTOTAL-HBZA200303002.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=自由共产主义简介 |url=https://libcom.org/library/ziyougongchanzhuyi |website=libcom.org |accessdate=2021-02-24 |archive-date=2021-01-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124134210/http://libcom.org/library/ziyougongchanzhuyi |dead-url=no }}</ref>（{{lang-en|free communism}}<ref>Price, Wayne (2002). [https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/wayne-price-what-is-anarchist-communism "What is Anarchist Communism?"] {{Wayback|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/wayne-price-what-is-anarchist-communism |date=20210225093036 }}. The Anarchist Library. Retrieved 2019-08-04. "Instead, Kropotkin proposed that a large city, during a revolution, “could organize itself on the lines of free communism; the city guaranteeing to every inhabitant dwelling, food, and clothing...in exchange for...five hour’s work; and...all those things which would be considered as luxuries might be obtained by everyone if he joins for the other half of the day all sorts of free associations....” (p.p. 118–119)".</ref>）、'''无政府主义共产主义'''（{{lang-en|anarchist communism}}<ref>{{cite book|title=The Spanish Civil War: Revolution and Counterrevolution|last=Bolloten|first=Burnett|year=1991|publisher=UNC Press Books|isbn=978-0-8078-1906-7|page=65|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-VarDLHA3_YC&pg=PA65&dq=%22libertarian+communism%22&q=%22libertarian%20communism%22|access-date=25 March 2011|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801065221/https://books.google.com/books?id=-VarDLHA3_YC&pg=PA65&dq=%22libertarian+communism%22&q=%22libertarian%20communism%22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Price, Wayne (2002). [https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/wayne-price-what-is-anarchist-communism "What is Anarchist Communism?"] {{Wayback|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/wayne-price-what-is-anarchist-communism |date=20210225093036 }}. The Anarchist Library. Retrieved 2019-08-04.</ref>）、'''[[自由意志主义|自由意志]]共产主义'''<ref>{{cite news |author1=反老孟 |author2=黄璞叶 |title=黑命攸关｜运动与暴力之辩：“糟得很”还是“好得很”？ |url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_7984910_1 |accessdate=2021-02-24 |work=[[澎湃新闻|澎湃新闻]] |date=2020-06-25 |archive-date=2021-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423092800/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_7984910_1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>（{{lang-en|libertarian communism}}<ref>According to anarchist historian [[Max_Nettlau|Max Nettlau]], the first use of the term "libertarian communism" was in November 1880, when a French anarchist congress employed it to more clearly identify its doctrines. {{cite book|title=A Short History of Anarchism|last=Nettlau|first=Max|author-link=Max Nettlau|year=1996|publisher=Freedom Press|isbn=978-0-900384-89-9|page=145}}</ref><ref>"Anarchist communism is also known as anarcho-communism, communist anarchism, or, sometimes, libertarian communism". [http://libcom.org/thought/anarchist-communism-an-introduction "Anarchist communism - an introduction"] {{Wayback|url=http://libcom.org/thought/anarchist-communism-an-introduction |date=20210308153554 }} by Libcom.org.</ref><ref>"The terms libertarian communism and anarchist communism thus became synonymous within the international anarchist movement as a result of the close connection they had in Spain (with libertarian communism becoming the prevalent term)". [http://www.fdca.it/fdcaen/historical/vault/ancom-libcom.htm "Anarchist Communism & Libertarian Communism" by Gruppo Comunista Anarchico di Firenze. from "L'informatore di parte", No.4, October 1979, quarterly journal of the Gruppo Comunista Anarchico di Firenze] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fdca.it/fdcaen/historical/vault/ancom-libcom.htm |date=20171018191416 }}.</ref><ref>"The 'Manifesto of Libertarian Communism' was written in 1953 by Georges Fontenis for the Federation Communiste Libertaire of France. It is one of the key texts of the anarchist-communist current". [http://libcom.org/library/manifesto-of-libertarian-communism-georges-fontenis "Manifesto of Libertarian Communism"] {{Wayback|url=http://libcom.org/library/manifesto-of-libertarian-communism-georges-fontenis |date=20191023030214 }} by Georges Fontenis.</ref><ref>"In 1926 a group of exiled Russian anarchists in France, the Delo Truda (Workers' Cause) group, published this pamphlet. It arose not from some academic study but from their experiences in the 1917 Russian revolution". [http://www.nestormakhno.info/english/platform/org_plat.htm "The Organizational Platform of the Libertarian Communists"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nestormakhno.info/english/platform/org_plat.htm |date=20210417165617 }} by Delo Truda.</ref>）}}<ref>{{cite journal |author1=于义永 |title=革命后的趋新：师复的无政府构想 |journal=《社会科学前沿》 |date=2019年 |volume=8 |issue=4 |url=https://m.hanspub.org/journal/paper/29673 |accessdate=2021-02-18 |archive-date=2021-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421041552/https://m.hanspub.org/journal/paper/29673 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=潘婉明 |title=在地 ∙ 跨域 ∙ 身体移动 ∙ 知识传播: 马来亚共产党史的再思考 |journal=《华人研究国际学报》 |date=2011 |volume=3 |issue=2 |pages=57-71 |doi=10.1142/S1793724811000162 |url=https://www.worldscientific.com/doi/abs/10.1142/S1793724811000162 |accessdate=2021-02-20}}</ref>（{{lang-en|anarcho-communism}}<ref>{{cite book |last1=Kinna |first1=Ruth |title=The Bloomsbury Companion to Anarchism |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dNuoAwAAQBAJ |date=2012-06-28 |publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing USA |isbn=978-1-4411-4270-2 |language=en |p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=dNuoAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA329&dq=Anarcho-communism&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiN__r73OnjAhVMy6QKHVeaDAYQ6AEIcTAJ#v=onepage&q=Anarcho-communism&f=false 329] |access-date=2021-02-17 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115214158/https://books.google.com/books?id=dNuoAwAAQBAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Hodges |first1=Donald C. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pu7zAgAAQBAJ |title=Sandino's Communism: Spiritual Politics for the Twenty-First Century |date=2014-02-01 |publisher=University of Texas Press |isbn=978-0-292-71564-6 |language=en |p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=Pu7zAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA3&dq=Anarcho-communism&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiN__r73OnjAhVMy6QKHVeaDAYQ6AEISjAE#v=onepage&q=Anarcho-communism&f=false 3] |access-date=2021-02-17 |archive-date=2021-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210722044609/https://books.google.com/books?id=Pu7zAgAAQBAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Wetherly |first1=Paul |title=Political Ideologies |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uXfJDgAAQBAJ |date=2017 |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-872785-9 |pp=[https://books.google.com/books?id=uXfJDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=political+ideologies&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiA3PKg3enjAhWRsKQKHaFMD-0Q6AEIKzAA#v=onepage&q=anarcho-communism&f=false 130], [https://books.google.it/books?id=uXfJDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=political+ideologies&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiA3PKg3enjAhWRsKQKHaFMD-0Q6AEIKzAA#v=snippet&q=anarcho-communism&f=false 137], [https://books.google.com/books?id=uXfJDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=political+ideologies&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiA3PKg3enjAhWRsKQKHaFMD-0Q6AEIKzAA#v=snippet&q=anarcho-communism&f=false 424] |language=en |access-date=2021-02-17 |archive-date=2021-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210722044620/https://books.google.com/books?id=uXfJDgAAQBAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Iliopoulos |first1=Christos |title=Nietzsche & Anarchism: An Elective Affinity and a Nietzschean reading of the December '08 revolt in Athens |date=2019-10-15 |publisher=Vernon Press |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PXOSDwAAQBAJ |isbn=978-1-62273-647-8 |p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=PXOSDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA35&dq=Anarcho-communism&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiN__r73OnjAhVMy6QKHVeaDAYQ6AEIUjAF#v=onepage&q=Anarcho-communism&f=false 35] |language=en |access-date=2021-02-17 |archive-date=2021-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210722045632/https://books.google.com/books?id=PXOSDwAAQBAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref>）是一种支持废除[[国家|国家]]、[[资本主义|资本主义]]、[[僱傭勞動|僱傭勞動]]、[[等级制度|等级制度]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Anarchist communism - an introduction|url=https://libcom.org/book/export/html/11558|access-date=2020-11-10|website=libcom.org|archive-date=2021-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210123144558/https://libcom.org/book/export/html/11558|dead-url=no}}</ref>及生产资料[[私有制|私有制]]（但无政府共产主义尊重在{{tsl|en|Collective ownership|Collective ownership|集体所有制}}下的[[動產|个人财产]]<ref>"The revolution abolishes private ownership of the means of production and distribution, and with it goes capitalistic business. Personal possession remains only in the things you use. Thus, your watch is your own, but the watch factory belongs to the people". [[亞歷山大·貝克曼|Alexander Berkman]]. "[[Now_and_After|What Is Communist Anarchism?]]" [http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1138] {{Wayback|url=http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1138 |date=20120523195452 }}.</ref>），同时拥护[[生产资料|生产资料]][[公有制|公有制]]<ref name=Mayne>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6MkTz6Rq7wUC&q=Communist+anarchism+belives+in+collective+ownership&pg=PA131|title=From Politics Past to Politics Future: An Integrated Analysis of Current and Emergent Paradigms|first=Alan James|last=Mayne|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|access-date=2010-09-20|isbn=978-0-275-96151-0|year=1999|archive-date=2021-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210327103934/https://books.google.com/books?id=6MkTz6Rq7wUC&q=Communist+anarchism+belives+in+collective+ownership&pg=PA131|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jeiudz5sBV4C&pg=PA14|page=14|title=Anarchism for Know-It-Alls By Know-It-Alls For Know-It-Alls, For Know-It-Alls|publisher=Filiquarian Publishing, LLC.|date=2008-01|access-date=2010-09-20|isbn=978-1-59986-218-7}}</ref>及由[[工人委員會|工人委員會]]所构成的横向网络所统领下依照[[各盡所能、各取所需|各盡所能、各取所需]]进行[[直接民主制|直接民主制]]<ref>[http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/worldwidemovements/fabbrianarandcom.html Fabbri, Luigi. "Anarchism and Communism." Northeastern Anarchist #4. 1922. 2002-10-13] {{Wayback|url=http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/worldwidemovements/fabbrianarandcom.html |date=20180929143950 }}.</ref><ref>Makhno, Mett, Arshinov, Valevski, Linski (Dielo Trouda). "The Organizational Platform of the Libertarian Communists". 1926. Constructive Section: available [http://www.nestormakhno.info/english/platform/constructive.htm here] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nestormakhno.info/english/platform/constructive.htm |date=20181002211517 }}.</ref>的[[政治哲学|政治哲学]]及{{tsl|en|Anarchist schools of thought|无政府主义思想流派|思想流派}}。其中的一些流派，比如{{tsl|en|insurrectionary anarchism|暴动无政府主义}}受[[利己无政府主义|利己主义]]和激进[[个人主义|个人主义]]影响颇深，并认为无政府共产主义是实现个人自由的最好社会组织形式<ref>Christopher Gray, ''Leaving the Twentieth Century'', p. 88.</ref><ref name="creativenothing">[http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Renzo_Novatore__Toward_the_Creative_Nothing.html "Towards the creative Nothing" by] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Renzo_Novatore__Toward_the_Creative_Nothing.html |date=20101128162745 }} [[Renzo_Novatore|Renzo Novatore]]</ref><ref name="bobblack">[[Post-left_anarchy|Post-left]] anarcho-communist [[Bob_Black|Bob Black]] after analysing [[Insurrectionary_anarchism|insurrectionary]] anarcho-communist [[鲁奇·加里尼|Luigi Galleani]]'s view on anarcho-communism went as far as saying that "communism is the final fulfillment of [[个人主义|individualism]]...The apparent contradiction between individualism and communism rests on a misunderstanding of both...Subjectivity is also objective: the individual really is subjective. It is nonsense to speak of "emphatically prioritizing the social over the individual,"...You may as well speak of prioritizing the chicken over the egg. Anarchy is a "method of individualization." It aims to combine the greatest individual development with the greatest communal unity."[http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Bob_Black__Nightmares_of_Reason.html#toc22 Bob Black. ''Nightmares of Reason''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Bob_Black__Nightmares_of_Reason.html#toc22 |date=20101027102331 }}.</ref><ref>"Modern Communists are more individualistic than Stirner. To them, not merely religion, morality, family and State are spooks, but property also is no more than a spook, in whose name the individual is enslaved - and how enslaved!...Communism thus creates a basis for the liberty and Eigenheit of the individual. I am a Communist because I am an Individualist. Fully as heartily the Communists concur with Stirner when he puts the word take in place of demand - that leads to the dissolution of property, to expropriation. Individualism and Communism go hand in hand". [http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/goldman/ME/mev2n3.html#142 "Stirner: The Ego and His Own"] {{Wayback|url=http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/goldman/ME/mev2n3.html#142 |date=20200405000744 }}. [[Max_Baginski|Max Baginski]]. ''[[大地_(雜誌)|Mother Earth]]''. Vol. 2. No. 3 May 1907.</ref>。大多数无政府共产主义者视无政府共产主义为一种调和个人与社会之间矛盾的方式<ref>"Communism is the one which guarantees the greatest amount of individual liberty — provided that the idea that begets the community be Liberty, Anarchy...Communism guarantees economic freedom better than any other form of association, because it can guarantee wellbeing, even luxury, in return for a few hours of work instead of a day's work". [http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=141 "Communism and Anarchy"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=141 |date=20211023194643 }} by [[彼得·阿列克谢耶维奇·克鲁泡特金|Peter Kropotkin]].</ref><ref>"This other society will be libertarian communism, in which social solidarity and free individuality find their full expression, and in which these two ideas develop in perfect harmony". [http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Dielo_Truda__Workers__Cause___Organisational_Platform_of_the_Libertarian_Communists.html ''Organisational Platform of the Libertarian Communists''] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/60XT5tf40?url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Dielo_Truda__Workers__Cause___Organisational_Platform_of_the_Libertarian_Communists.html |date=20110729121456 |dateformat=iso }} by Dielo Truda (Workers' Cause).</ref><ref>"I see the dichotomies made between individualism and communism, individual revolt and class struggle, the struggle against human exploitation and the exploitation of nature as false dichotomies and feel that those who accept them are impoverishing their own critique and struggle". [http://www.reocities.com/kk_abacus/vb/wd12persp.html "My Perspectives"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101202053009/http://www.reocities.com/kk_abacus/vb/wd12persp.html |date=2010-12-02 }} by Willful Disobedience Vol. 2, No. 12.</ref><ref name="BrownPolitics">[[L._Susan_Brown|L. Susan Brown]], ''[[The_Politics_of_Individualism|The Politics of Individualism]]'', Black Rose Books (2002).</ref><ref name="BrownWork">[[L._Susan_Brown|L. Susan Brown]], [http://www.spunk.org/texts/writers/brown/sp001735.html "Does Work Really Work?"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.spunk.org/texts/writers/brown/sp001735.html |date=20160303165817 }}.</ref>。

无政府共产主义发展自[[法国大革命|法国大革命]]后的{{tsl|en|Political radicalism|政治激进主义|激进}}[[社会主义|社会主义]]潮流<ref name="Graham-2005"/><ref>[http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=211 "Chapter 41: The Anarchists"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=211 |date=20211023194645 }} in ''The Great French Revolution 1789-1793'' by Peter Kropotkin.</ref>，但直到[[第一国际|第一国际]]在意大利的分部成立后才成型<ref name="Nunzio Pernicone pp. 111-113">Nunzio Pernicone, ''Italian Anarchism 1864–1892'', pp. 111-113, AK Press 2009.</ref>。俄国思想家[[克魯泡特金|克魯泡特金]]在無政府共產主義中影响力十分巨大，并影响到了其后的内部分化<ref name=" Alain Pengam">[https://web.archive.org/web/20090312022528/http://www.zabalaza.net/theory/txt_anok_comm_ap.htm "Anarchist-Communism" by Alain Pengam]: "This inability to break definitively with collectivism in all its forms also exhibited itself over the question of the workers' movement, which divided anarchist-communism into a number of tendencies."</ref>。迄今为止，最知名的无政府共产主义社群例包含{{tsl|en|Spanish Revolution of 1936|1936年西班牙革命}}中的无政府工团主义地区<ref>"This process of education and class organization, more than any single factor in Spain, produced the collectives. And to the degree that the [[全國勞工聯盟|CNT]]-[[伊比利亚无政府主义联合会|FAI]] (for the two organizations became fatally coupled after July 1936) exercised the major influence in an area, the collectives proved to be generally more durable, communist and resistant to Stalinist counterrevolution than other republican-held areas of Spain." [http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1045 Murray Bookchin] {{Wayback|url=http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1045 |date=20211023194646 }}. ''To Remember Spain: The Anarchist and Syndicalist Revolution of 1936'']</ref>及在1918年至1921年[[俄国内战|俄国内战]]中由[[乌克兰革命起义军|乌克兰革命者]][[内斯托尔·伊万诺维奇·马赫诺|内斯托尔·伊万诺维奇·马赫诺]]所统领的[[自由地區_(烏克蘭)|乌克兰自由地区]]。乌克兰自由地区受克鲁泡特金著作中的无政府共产主义及[[集體無政府主義|集體無政府主義]]影响极大，且一度击退[[俄国白军|白军]]和[[苏联红军|红军]]，统治乌克兰的大多数地区，但最终被[[布尔什维克|布尔什维克]]所占领<ref>Skirda, Alexandre (2004). ''[https://www.google.com/books/edition/Nestor_Makhno_anarchy_s_Cossack/pMji9s9WOlwC?hl=en&gbpv=0 Nestor Makhno: Anarchy's Cossack]''. AK Press. pp. 86. 236–238.</ref>。

1929年，韩国无政府共产主义联合会在崇尚[[无政府主义|无政府主义]]和[[独立|独立]][[行动主义|行动主义]]的[[將軍_(軍銜)|將軍]][[金佐鎮|金佐鎮]]的支持下一度建立了一个{{tsl|en|Korean People's Association in Manchuria|在满韩族总联合会|无政府共产主义社会}}，但最终随着大日本帝国暗杀了金佐鎮并自南方入侵该地区，同时[[中國國民黨|中國國民黨]]从北部入侵该地区，该地区很快便丧失了自治权，最终被并入大日本帝国的附庸[[满洲国|满洲国]]。在1936年开始的[[西班牙内战|西班牙内战]]中，{{tsl|en|Anarchism in Spain|无政府主义在西班牙|西班牙无政府主义者}}经过在西班牙革命期间的努力和影响，一度在[[阿拉貢地區防禦委員會|阿拉贡的多数地区建立了一个无政府主义社会]]，并且将无政府共产主义传播至了雷凡特、安达卢西亚及[[西班牙内战中的无政府主义加泰罗尼亚|加泰罗尼亚]]，但最终被[[弗朗西斯科·佛朗哥独裁|佛朗哥]]所统领的[[國民軍_(西班牙內戰)|國民軍]]所击败<ref name="Spain 1936">[http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1045 Murray Bookchin] {{Wayback|url=http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1045 |date=20211023194646 }}. ''To Remember Spain: The Anarchist and Syndicalist Revolution of 1936''</ref>。

